│ The `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` function is      │
│ responsible for determining whether the VPlan contains any   │
│ simplifications not accounted for in the legacy cost model.  │
│ The issue lies in its inability to handle certain symbolic   │
│ expressions or skipped instructions, leading to the          │
│ assertion failure in `computeBestVF`.                        │
│                                                              │
│ To address this, I will enhance the                          │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` function to better   │
│ handle symbolic loop bounds and ensure all relevant          │
│ instructions are analyzed. Additionally, I will add          │
│ debugging information to log the results of the function and │
│ the contents of `SeenInstrs` and `skipCostComputation`.      │
│                                                              │
